  schema:name "Determinant" ;
  schema:description "The determinant is a single number you can compute from a square [matrix](./matrix.md) that tells you something fundamental about the [linear map](./linear-map.md) the matrix represents: whether it collapses space, and if not, by how much it scales volumes and whether it flips orientation." ;
